			<div class="content" id="post-content-3766509">
									

<p>DrMagnus is absolutely correct about the scientific parts of US government. From personal knowledge, it's not true in the accounting/billing parts or Internal Business parts.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-687412-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-687412-1')">1</a></sup> I've heard military use kilometers and pounds in the same sentence, so I think SI use is uneven there. I assume Federal Law enforcement would be similar to military use.</p>
<p>My guess is that standard UIU format would be to use both, as</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Item weighs 110 pounds (50&#160;kg). Item affects area within a radius of 6 miles (10&#160;km).</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That, or the reverse, pretty common in US-centric publications. From a OOC perspective, it says this is American, without alienating International readers.</p>
